<br>
Yes, the fire thing really, uh hem, burned me....<br>
<br>
I had been collecting D&amp;D stuff since about '79. I only used one set of books to play D&amp;D with, so all the doubles and triples of stuff I had were put away purposely in an attempt to make a collection of stuff. So basically I not only lost the books I used to play D&amp;D with, but I lost the stuff I had spent years collecting too.<br>
<br>
Do you or anyone else have any sites or other suggestions on where to find old D&amp;D stuff? I've looked at stuff on Ebay, but most of what I've seen there is either obviously not in great shape or the pictures arent good enough to tell one way or the other. Is there another resource out there for someone who wants to get back into collecting D&amp;D stuff, or is it basically catch as catch can?<br>
<br>
I've kinda been out of the loop awhile, only started playing again 2 years ago and that was with 3rd edition (which I'm not totally thrilled with). I'd like to start my collection back up again but I dont see D&amp;D stuff around any where..<br>
<br>
Any pointers where to start looking would be great.<br>
<br>
