<br>
The best place to find old D&amp;D stuff is yard sales and gaming conventions. People at gaming conventions know the real value of a product, and will cost a little more than a yard sale, but it wont be as random. There are a few online stores that sell used stuff, but I have never purchased from them so I can't guarantee the results. EBay is a great place to look for some things, but not gaming stuff. People who EBAY old D&amp;D stuff think they &quot;have something&quot; and you pay too much for inferior product. Mint condition 1st edition books can draw in up to $100 for unearthed arcana and the first Dieties and Demigods (there were two versions, I believe the chulthu mythos were not in the second one but I dont remember off hand), but no more than $75 for any of the others. Any comic collector knows that MINT is VERY hard to find. So most of what you will find is worth no more that half that, and a lot is not even worth cover price. The pricing information is a couple years old, but they printed a TON of that material, and most of it was well used. Last I checked there was no official price list for the stuff, so when people trade in it, you don't have anything to go by like the Cards, Coins or Comics. If there IS and official list that somebody has found, let me know, I would love to put my hands on it.     <p><IMG SRC="http://www.fantasygamingworld.com/pics/thurmsig.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useaghankai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seaghan Kai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/02 5:30:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17753.topic&index=156>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.comixtreme.com/Marvel/Ultimate%20Marvel/headshots/jackrussell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NWN</span><hr size=1> I don't know if this has been posted yet, but they already have their 1st module online:<br>
<br>
BioWare has released the first official add-on module for Neverwinter Nights, its recently released Dungeons &amp; Dragons role-playing game. The module, Contest of Champions, lets a group of players fight each other on up to four different teams. It features two different no-holds-barred battle arenas, and the last team standing at the end of combat wins the round. <br>
<br>
Players will be able to enter their team headquarters and purchase items and equipment within adjustable limits to prepare for the contest. They can then teleport into the battle arenas with the rest of their team. Once all their opponents are defeated, they will be teleported back to their headquarters<br>
<br>
